powershell
# CHECK FOR EMAIL EXPORTS AND BUSINESS DOCUMENTS
Write-Host "=== CHECKING FOR EMAIL EXPORTS AND BUSINESS FILES ===" -ForegroundColor Yellow

# Search for common business file locations
$businessFolders = @(
    "$env:USERPROFILE\Desktop",
    "$env:USERPROFILE\Documents", 
    "$env:USERPROFILE\Downloads",
    "C:\MASTER_DOSSIER",
    "C:\EMERGENCY_BACKUP_20251025_121921"
)

foreach ($folder in $businessFolders) {
    if (Test-Path $folder) {
        Write-Host "Searching in: $folder" -ForegroundColor Green
        Get-ChildItem -Path $folder -Recurse -Include "*.pdf","*.xls","*.xlsx","*.doc","*.docx","*.csv","*.txt" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue |
        Where-Object { 
            $_.Name -notlike "*vim*" -and 
            $_.Name -notlike "*quotes.txt*" -and
            ($_.Name -like "*longo*" -or $_.Name -like "*construction*" -or $_.Name -like "*estimate*" -or $_.Name -like "*invoice*")
        } |
        Select-Object FullName, LastWriteTime, @{Name="SizeKB";Expression={[math]::Round($_.Length/1KB,2)}}
    }
}

    if ($content) {
        foreach ($term in $searchTerms) {
            if ($content -match $term) {
                Write-Host "FOUND '$term' in: $($_.FullName)" -ForegroundColor Green
                # Show context around the match
                $lines = $content -split "`n"
                for ($i = 0; $i -lt $lines.Count; $i++) {
                    if ($lines[$i] -match $term) {
                        $start = [Math]::Max(0, $i - 2)
                        $end = [Math]::Min($lines.Count - 1, $i + 2)
                        Write-Host "  Context:" -ForegroundColor Yellow
                        for ($j = $start; $j -le $end; $j++) {
                            Write-Host "    Line $($j+1): $($lines[$j])" -ForegroundColor White
                        }
                        break
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
